Police have rescued 36 young girls from a house in Pakistan after they were taken hostage from their school in a bizarre debt row involving their teacher.

Officers found the girls, aged between eight and 14, after they had been secretly moved to the capital Karachi from their rural madrassa without their parents' knowledge.

The children were reportedly boarding at the school under the supervision of a teacher who was in dispute with the owner of the house over non-payment of a debt.

