Others say she was using them as leverage to force him to pay the money back directly.

The girls were taken into care by the Senior Superintendent of Police and are being returned to their families, who learned of their disappearance yesterday.

Two men have been arrested for their alleged involvement in transporting the girls to Karachi.  

The madrassa owner reportedly told police that she regularly took the children to Karachi to further their education.

